{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"38c11999-991f-414c-9bec-545ef361e92f","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` — it re-runs tests automatically whenever you save a file:\n\n```\ndotnet watch test --filter \"RemoveStock_ExceedsAvailable_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThe `--filter` flag limits it to just the failing test for faster feedback. Drop the filter when you're ready to run the full suite.\n\n**About the bug:** `RemoveStock` never throws — it just subtracts, even when quantity exceeds stock. You'll need to add a guard, e.g.:\n\n```csharp\npublic void RemoveStock(string sku, int quantity)\n{\n    var current = _stock.GetValueOrDefault(sku);\n    if (quantity > current)\n        throw new InvalidOperationException(\"Insufficient stock\");\n    _stock[sku] = current - quantity;\n}\n```\n\nWould you like me to apply that fix?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e2c1c1bc-695a-4ff9-887e-a79cbd8b5ffa","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to set up hot reload for rapid iteration. With `dotnet watch` and MSTest on .NET 10 with the Microsoft.Testing.Platform runner, they can use `dotnet watch test` to automatically re-run tests when files change.\n\nLet me tell them how to do this and also quickly note the bug (RemoveStock doesn't throw when exceeding available stock).","outputTokens":304,"requestId":"3415:1BDA61:B51396:D45F67:69F4048A"},"id":"2abca1a4-9edf-40c5-b78a-c90ab286440a","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:40:35.215Z","parentId":"ac586da7-f884-414d-ad3c-329afc655b2d"}
